					<div id="post-69" class="post-69 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized">
						<div style="float:right;">
							<a href="index.html?p=61" rel="prev"><img class="prevNext" src="../images/previous.gif" width="27" height="32" alt="previous post" title="previous post" /></a><a href="index.html?p=74" rel="next"> <img class="prevNext" src="../images/next.gif" width="27" height="32" alt="next post" title="next post" /></a>						</div>
						<h2 style="margin-right:3em;" class="entry-title">Fire risk management and protection strategies training offered in Burlington</h2>
	
						<div class="entry-meta">
							<p class="slug">Posted January 31, 2014 <!--by admin--></p>						</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
	
						<div class="entry-content">
							<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2014/01/fire_steeple.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-9488" style="padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; float: right; border: 0pt;" alt="fire_steeple" src="wp-content/uploads/2014/01/fire_steeple-300x183.jpg" width="300" height="183" /></a>Burlington’s Certified Local Government will be hosting Nick Artim (Heritage Protection Group) and Jack Watts Ph.D. (Fire Safety Institute) for a daylong seminar on Fire Risk Management and Protection Strategies March 6, 2014 at Main Street Landing.</p>
<p>The seminar is aimed at owners and operators of historic properties, code officials, preservation architects, first responders and firemen, contractors, property managers and caretakers, planners, and anyone interested in fire safety, safe practices, and effective strategies to mitigate fire risk.</p>
<p><a title="announcement" href="http://www.vhfa.org/documents/housing_matters/2014/fire%20seminar%20announcement.pdf">Read more. </a></p>
													</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
		
